00:11:22,718 --> 00:11:24,584
Now that Misa's
away from the crowd,

260
00:11:24,618 --> 00:11:27,851
I just have to give her a call
and ask for L's real name.

261
00:11:27,884 --> 00:11:28,818
-Bye, Light.

262
00:11:28,851 --> 00:11:30,251
I'll see you after
I'm done work.

263
00:11:30,284 --> 00:11:32,484
Miss you already. [giggle]

264
00:11:37,184 --> 00:11:37,951
-Now, then.

265
00:11:37,984 --> 00:11:39,718
Perhaps we should get going.

266
00:11:39,751 --> 00:11:41,118
-Yeah.

267
00:11:41,151 --> 00:11:42,618
Actually, could you go on ahead?

268
00:11:42,651 --> 00:11:44,384
I need to go use the restroom.

269
00:11:44,418 --> 00:11:45,684
-Oh, OK, then.

270
00:11:45,718 --> 00:11:46,651
I'll see you there.

271
00:12:00,684 --> 00:12:02,884
LIGHT (VOICEOVER): It's over.

272
00:12:02,918 --> 00:12:08,051
It's been fun, L. I'm
grateful that I was the one

273
00:12:08,084 --> 00:12:11,184
to discover your name, so
I could kill you myself.

274
00:12:29,038 --> 00:12:32,405
L, it's been fun.

275
00:12:32,438 --> 00:12:35,338
I'm grateful that I was the
one to discover your name,

276
00:12:35,372 --> 00:12:37,005
so I could kill you myself.

277
00:12:42,872 --> 00:12:47,772
[phone ringing]

278
00:12:47,805 --> 00:12:53,705
[ringtone]

279
00:13:05,138 --> 00:13:07,072
-Yes?

280
00:13:07,105 --> 00:13:08,572
Hello?

281
00:13:08,605 --> 00:13:10,238
-What do you mean, hello?

282
00:13:10,272 --> 00:13:11,938
-Oh, is that you, Light.

283
00:13:11,972 --> 00:13:14,805
I guess must have dropped this
phone in all of the commotion

284
00:13:14,838 --> 00:13:15,872
earlier on.

285
00:13:15,905 --> 00:13:17,172
LIGHT (VOICEOVER): He took it.

286
00:13:17,205 --> 00:13:17,672
Bastard.

287
00:13:22,305 --> 00:13:24,038
-Uh, hello?

288
00:13:24,072 --> 00:13:27,272
LIGHT (ON PHONE): Yeah, that's--
that's Misa's cell phone you

289
00:13:27,305 --> 00:13:28,038
have.

290
00:13:28,072 --> 00:13:29,038
I can give it back to her.

291
00:13:29,072 --> 00:13:29,872
-Oh, I see.

292
00:13:29,905 --> 00:13:30,838
Sure, that makes sense.

293
00:13:36,472 --> 00:13:38,272
LIGHT (VOICEOVER):
Ryuga, he probably thinks

294
00:13:38,305 --> 00:13:39,972
he's pretty clever right now.

295
00:13:40,005 --> 00:13:42,772
But Misa has another phone
he doesn't know about.

296
00:13:42,805 --> 00:13:44,938
I'll just call that one instead.

297
00:13:44,972 --> 00:13:45,905
[phone ringing]

298
00:13:45,938 --> 00:13:47,272
L: Oh.

299
00:13:47,305 --> 00:13:50,738
Oh, this time's it's actually
my cell phone. [clears throat]

300
00:13:50,772 --> 00:13:51,672
Yes?

301
00:13:51,705 --> 00:13:53,405
Yes, I see.

302
00:13:53,438 --> 00:13:56,238
So it's done then?

303
00:13:56,272 --> 00:13:56,772
I understand.

304
00:14:00,072 --> 00:14:02,072
I'm not exactly sure
how you'll take this,

305
00:14:02,105 --> 00:14:03,638
but regarding Misa
Amane, there's

306
00:14:03,672 --> 00:14:05,338
something you should know.

307
00:14:05,372 --> 00:14:07,572
We've taken her into
custody under suspicion

308
00:14:07,605 --> 00:14:10,038
of being the second Kira.

309
00:14:10,072 --> 00:14:11,405
RYUK: [laughs]

310
00:14:11,438 --> 00:14:14,105
LIGHT (VOICEOVER): How long
has he known about Misa?

311
00:14:14,138 --> 00:14:17,338
I never thought he'd
find her this quickly.

312
00:14:17,372 --> 00:14:19,772
-We gathered physical
evidence from the envelopes

313
00:14:19,805 --> 00:14:21,805
that were sent by
the second Kira.

314
00:14:21,838 --> 00:14:24,338
In particular, we
recovered hairs and fibers

315
00:14:24,372 --> 00:14:26,472
from the masking tape
used to seal them.

316
00:14:26,505 --> 00:14:29,005
They matched what we
found in Misa's room.

317
00:14:29,038 --> 00:14:30,872
There would be a public
uproar if it gets out

318
00:14:30,905 --> 00:14:33,372
that she's been apprehended
as the second Kira.

319
00:14:33,405 --> 00:14:36,572
So officially, we've charged her
manager with drug possession,

320
00:14:36,605 --> 00:14:38,605
and she's a voluntary witness.

321
00:14:38,638 --> 00:14:40,138
But I doubt any of
this will get out.

322
00:14:43,372 --> 00:14:44,738
LIGHT (VOICEOVER):
I was careless.

323
00:14:44,772 --> 00:14:47,605
The videos-- I should have
destroyed all the evidence

324
00:14:47,638 --> 00:14:50,572
before the police had a
chance to go through it.

325
00:14:50,605 --> 00:14:53,805
In the end, Ryuga knew
that his best defense

326
00:14:53,838 --> 00:14:56,605
was to stay close to me,
rather than trying to hide.

327
00:14:56,638 --> 00:14:59,038
He confronted things head on.

328
00:14:59,072 --> 00:15:02,372
This wager was my--

329
00:15:02,405 --> 00:15:04,038
L (VOICEOVER): Was my--

330
00:15:04,072 --> 00:15:07,238
LIGHT (VOICEOVER):
Was my-- [gasp]

331
00:15:07,272 --> 00:15:09,638
-Hm?

332
00:15:09,672 --> 00:15:11,005
LIGHT (VOICEOVER): Not yet.

333
00:15:11,038 --> 00:15:13,636
The real battle is
just beginning, L.

334
00:15:23,572 --> 00:15:25,938
-Watari, has she
said anything yet?

335
00:15:25,972 --> 00:15:28,338
WATARI (ON SPEAKER): No,
she hasn't spoken a word.

336
00:15:28,372 --> 00:15:30,338
L: Get me a visual
of her, will you?

337
00:15:30,372 --> 00:15:31,738
WATARI (ON SPEAKER):
Are you sure?

338
00:15:31,772 --> 00:15:32,272
L: Yes.

339
00:15:32,305 --> 00:15:34,638
And quickly.

340
00:15:34,672 --> 00:15:36,505
[gasping]

341
00:15:36,538 --> 00:15:41,338
[crying]

342
00:15:41,372 --> 00:15:44,805
MAN: Ryuzaki, what's
the meaning of this?

343
00:15:44,838 --> 00:15:46,505
L: I've Apprehended
her on suspicion

344
00:15:46,538 --> 00:15:47,972
of being the second Kira.

345
00:15:48,005 --> 00:15:50,272
I'm afraid thinks is necessary.

346
00:15:50,305 --> 00:15:52,538
-Chances are, Amane is guilty.

347
00:15:52,572 --> 00:15:54,538
There seems to be enough
evidence to convict her.

348
00:15:54,572 --> 00:15:56,638
But all the same.

349
00:15:56,672 --> 00:15:58,905
-Yes, there can be no mistake.

350
00:15:58,938 --> 00:16:01,238
Now we need a
confession out of her.

351
00:16:01,272 --> 00:16:04,105
We need to know how she
kills, whether she knows Kira,

352
00:16:04,138 --> 00:16:06,505
and if so, who he really is.

353
00:16:06,538 --> 00:16:08,938
Watari, take the
necessary precautions.

354
00:16:08,972 --> 00:16:12,438
But beyond that, you're free to
do whatever has to be done, OK?

355
00:16:12,472 --> 00:16:13,272
Just make her speak.

356
00:16:13,305 --> 00:16:14,572
WATARI (ON SPEAKER): Very well.

357
00:16:14,605 --> 00:16:15,505
L: Oh, and Mr. Yagami?

358
00:16:15,538 --> 00:16:16,538
-Huh?

359
00:16:16,572 --> 00:16:18,738
L: Light has now become
our prime suspect.

360
00:16:18,772 --> 00:16:21,072
And I'm probably going to
bring him in for interrogation

361
00:16:21,105 --> 00:16:22,205
as well.

362
00:16:22,238 --> 00:16:23,672
Please be prepared for that.

363
00:16:43,705 --> 00:16:46,138
WATARI (ON SPEAKER):
Ryuzaki, Amane is talking.

364
00:16:46,172 --> 00:16:47,405
-Huh?

365
00:16:47,438 --> 00:16:50,238
Quickly, get me a
visual and audio.

366
00:16:50,272 --> 00:16:51,572
[grunt]

367
00:16:51,605 --> 00:16:54,272
MAN: Finally, after
three days of this, huh?

368
00:16:54,305 --> 00:16:59,126
[crying] I-- I can't
take it anymore.

369
00:17:00,772 --> 00:17:02,172
Kill me.

370
00:17:02,205 --> 00:17:03,105
-Huh?

371
00:17:03,138 --> 00:17:04,238
-Kill me.

372
00:17:04,272 --> 00:17:06,705
Please just kill me.

373
00:17:06,738 --> 00:17:08,005
-I don't know.

374
00:17:08,038 --> 00:17:10,538
Maybe this was all too much
for a young girl to take.

375
00:17:10,572 --> 00:17:11,305
-He's right.

376
00:17:11,338 --> 00:17:13,872
We've pushed her too far.

377
00:17:13,905 --> 00:17:16,905
ROBOT: Misa Amane,
can you hear me?

378
00:17:16,938 --> 00:17:18,038
-I hear you.

379
00:17:18,072 --> 00:17:21,372
Please, just kill me now.

380
00:17:21,405 --> 00:17:23,538
-Does this mean you admit
to being the second Kira?

381
00:17:23,572 --> 00:17:25,638
Is this the reason
you wish to die.

382
00:17:25,672 --> 00:17:26,772
-No.

383
00:17:26,805 --> 00:17:29,738
I don't know anything
about the second Kira.

384
00:17:29,772 --> 00:17:31,972
I really can't
take this anymore.

385
00:17:32,005 --> 00:17:34,272
I'd rather be dead.

386
00:17:34,305 --> 00:17:36,872
Now hurry up and kill me!

387
00:17:36,905 --> 00:17:42,438
If you wanted to, you could
kill me right now, couldn't you?

388
00:17:42,472 --> 00:17:44,638
-Misa, do you mean--

389
00:17:44,672 --> 00:17:45,538
-Yes.

390
00:17:45,572 --> 00:17:46,538
Kill me.

391
00:17:46,572 --> 00:17:49,572
-Do you really mean that, Misa?

392
00:17:49,605 --> 00:17:53,072
-Yes, I do.

393
00:17:53,105 --> 00:17:55,605
[sigh] I can't take it anymore.

394
00:17:55,638 --> 00:17:57,572
Kill me.

395
00:17:57,605 --> 00:18:00,705
-If I do this, then
Light Yagami dies, too.

396
00:18:00,738 --> 00:18:02,305
This is all his fault.

397
00:18:02,338 --> 00:18:03,338
-You can't.

398
00:18:03,372 --> 00:18:04,472
No, you can't.

399
00:18:04,505 --> 00:18:06,072
Please, just kill me.

400
00:18:06,105 --> 00:18:07,672
-Why, Misa?

401
00:18:07,705 --> 00:18:11,405
Why do you want to die for him?

402
00:18:11,438 --> 00:18:12,305
MISA: Fine!

403
00:18:12,338 --> 00:18:14,638
If you won't kill me--

404
00:18:14,672 --> 00:18:15,638
-Stop her!

405
00:18:15,672 --> 00:18:16,805
Watari, don't let
her bite her tongue.

406
00:18:16,838 --> 00:18:19,438
[muffled yelling]

407
00:18:24,072 --> 00:18:25,472
-Is it possible
that this behavior

408
00:18:25,505 --> 00:18:27,138
could be attributed
to Kira controlling

409
00:18:27,172 --> 00:18:30,405
her actions before death?

410
00:18:30,438 --> 00:18:32,938
-Oh, what's the matter, Rem?

411
00:18:35,638 --> 00:18:39,705
-Light Yagami, Misa
has refused my offer

412
00:18:39,738 --> 00:18:42,872
to help her escape, no
doubt because she knows

413
00:18:42,905 --> 00:18:45,605
it would cause you trouble,
since the police would then

414
00:18:45,638 --> 00:18:48,272
have proof of her powers.

415
00:18:48,305 --> 00:18:51,672
When her suffering became
more than she could bear,

416
00:18:51,705 --> 00:18:55,938
she started begging
me to kill her.

417
00:18:55,972 --> 00:18:59,205
All of this because she
wants you to love her.

418
00:19:02,105 --> 00:19:05,472
I could not possibly
let it go on like that.

419
00:19:05,505 --> 00:19:07,972
I couldn't bring
myself to do it.

420
00:19:08,005 --> 00:19:12,505
There was only one way to
save her from her suffering.

421
00:19:12,538 --> 00:19:15,372
-Forfeiting ownership
of the Death Note.

422
00:19:15,405 --> 00:19:16,505
-Yes.

423
00:19:16,538 --> 00:19:19,838
If Misa forfeits ownership
of the Death Note,

424
00:19:19,872 --> 00:19:22,705
all her memories related
to it would disappear.

425
00:19:22,738 --> 00:19:26,272
All the murders she
committed with it, the fact

426
00:19:26,305 --> 00:19:30,138
that you are Kira-- all
those memories would be gone.

427
00:19:30,172 --> 00:19:31,805
Your secret would be safe.

428
00:19:34,338 --> 00:19:38,572
Also, Misa would no longer be
able to Ryuk or me, either.

429
00:19:41,238 --> 00:19:45,138
Misa, when this is done,
you'll forget everything

430
00:19:45,172 --> 00:19:47,805
about Shinigami
and the Death Note.

431
00:19:47,838 --> 00:19:50,172
-[whimpering]

432
00:19:50,205 --> 00:19:51,505
-It's OK.

433
00:19:51,538 --> 00:19:55,605
The human being who you
love is Light Yagami.

434
00:19:55,638 --> 00:19:57,605
I promise those
feelings will remain.

435
00:20:00,972 --> 00:20:05,205
So Misa, forfeit ownership
of the Death Note,

436
00:20:05,238 --> 00:20:09,538
and leave everything
to Light Yagami.

437
00:20:09,572 --> 00:20:10,038
-Mhm.

438
00:20:28,772 --> 00:20:31,172
-Huh?

439
00:20:31,205 --> 00:20:31,672
Hm.

440
00:20:39,638 --> 00:20:44,005
-And so Misa is no longer
the owner of a Death Note.

441
00:20:44,038 --> 00:20:45,805
-You did the right thing, Rem.

442
00:20:45,838 --> 00:20:47,372
I was beginning
to think that was

443
00:20:47,405 --> 00:20:49,905
the only way out
of this situation.

444
00:20:49,938 --> 00:20:51,838
If her memories
of the Death Note

445
00:20:51,872 --> 00:20:53,305
are gone, than
chances are, they'll

446
00:20:53,338 --> 00:20:56,005
have to release her eventually.

447
00:20:56,038 --> 00:20:58,738
-Light Yagami, I
proposed this to Misa,

448
00:20:58,772 --> 00:21:00,872
knowing it was exactly
what you wanted

449
00:21:00,905 --> 00:21:02,905
and that it would
serve your purposes.

450
00:21:02,938 --> 00:21:05,472
But I did so on one condition.

451
00:21:05,505 --> 00:21:09,938
And that is, if you don't
save Misa, I will kill you.

452
00:21:18,672 --> 00:21:20,572
-I understand.

453
00:21:20,605 --> 00:21:24,138
And I have a pretty good
idea what L will do next.

454
00:21:24,172 --> 00:21:25,438
I have a plan.

455
00:21:27,972 --> 00:21:31,538
This is goodbye, Ryuk.

456
00:21:31,572 --> 00:21:32,038
Huh?

457
00:21:39,034 --> 00:21:42,468
[theme music]

458
00:22:51,668 --> 00:22:54,401
LIGHT (VOICEOVER): Yeah, I know
I must look pretty bad in here.

459
00:22:54,434 --> 00:22:57,334
But this useless
pride, I suppose

460
00:22:57,368 --> 00:23:02,201
I'll have to get rid of it.

